        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 8 at 8:08PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 807 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles northwest of Suncrest, or 26 miles northwest of Spokane, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Springdale, Diamond Lake, Sacheen Lake, Ford, Dalkena, Loon Lake, and
Clayton.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 2 in Washington between mile markers 314 and 329.
U.S. Highway 395 in Washington between mile markers 183 and 193.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
